{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/eng/deeplearning/25-07-28/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>I visualized the high-level operation of Gemini CLI and Claude Code using mermaid diagrams.</p>\n<h3 id=\"gemini-cli\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#gemini-cli\" aria-label=\"gemini cli permalink\" class=\"anchor-header before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Gemini CLI</h3>\n<p>I directly prompted Gemini CLI to \"visualize the overall flow of gemini cli as a mermaid diagram,\" and then asked it to \"review whether the result matches your (gemini cli's) actual logic.\"</p>\n<p>Please note that hallucinations may exist, so treat this as reference material only.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 760px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/2ab717ac05af19fa2095bf44ae995979/29007/25-07-28-1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 293.1578947368421%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/2ab717ac05af19fa2095bf44ae995979/15813/25-07-28-1.webp 190w,\n/static/2ab717ac05af19fa2095bf44ae995979/1cdb2/25-07-28-1.webp 380w,\n/static/2ab717ac05af19fa2095bf44ae995979/9046c/25-07-28-1.webp 760w,\n/static/2ab717ac05af19fa2095bf44ae995979/c89f9/25-07-28-1.webp 1140w,\n/static/2ab717ac05af19fa2095bf44ae995979/7afe4/25-07-28-1.webp 1520w,\n/static/2ab717ac05af19fa2095bf44ae995979/fad48/25-07-28-1.webp 1600w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/2ab717ac05af19fa2095bf44ae995979/a2d4f/25-07-28-1.png 190w,\n/static/2ab717ac05af19fa2095bf44ae995979/3f520/25-07-28-1.png 380w,\n/static/2ab717ac05af19fa2095bf44ae995979/3c051/25-07-28-1.png 760w,\n/static/2ab717ac05af19fa2095bf44ae995979/b5cea/25-07-28-1.png 1140w,\n/static/2ab717ac05af19fa2095bf44ae995979/891d5/25-07-28-1.png 1520w,\n/static/2ab717ac05af19fa2095bf44ae995979/29007/25-07-28-1.png 1600w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/2ab717ac05af19fa2095bf44ae995979/3c051/25-07-28-1.png\"\n            alt=\"img\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h3 id=\"claude-code\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#claude-code\" aria-label=\"claude code permalink\" class=\"anchor-header before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Claude Code</h3>\n<p>The overall flow below was taken from the following link, and this person also prompted Claude Code directly to describe its own flow.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/abhinavsharma/claude-code-description?tab=readme-ov-file\">https://github.com/abhinavsharma/claude-code-description?tab=readme-ov-file</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 760px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/417b318d7714940271bfa835491025fd/29007/25-07-28-2.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 366.3157894736842%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/417b318d7714940271bfa835491025fd/15813/25-07-28-2.webp 190w,\n/static/417b318d7714940271bfa835491025fd/1cdb2/25-07-28-2.webp 380w,\n/static/417b318d7714940271bfa835491025fd/9046c/25-07-28-2.webp 760w,\n/static/417b318d7714940271bfa835491025fd/c89f9/25-07-28-2.webp 1140w,\n/static/417b318d7714940271bfa835491025fd/7afe4/25-07-28-2.webp 1520w,\n/static/417b318d7714940271bfa835491025fd/fad48/25-07-28-2.webp 1600w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/417b318d7714940271bfa835491025fd/a2d4f/25-07-28-2.png 190w,\n/static/417b318d7714940271bfa835491025fd/3f520/25-07-28-2.png 380w,\n/static/417b318d7714940271bfa835491025fd/3c051/25-07-28-2.png 760w,\n/static/417b318d7714940271bfa835491025fd/b5cea/25-07-28-2.png 1140w,\n/static/417b318d7714940271bfa835491025fd/891d5/25-07-28-2.png 1520w,\n/static/417b318d7714940271bfa835491025fd/29007/25-07-28-2.png 1600w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/417b318d7714940271bfa835491025fd/3c051/25-07-28-2.png\"\n            alt=\"img\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h5 id=\"claude-code-in-detail\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#claude-code-in-detail\" aria-label=\"claude code in detail permalink\" class=\"anchor-header before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Claude Code in Detail</h5>\n<p>There is also someone who analyzed and visualized the Claude Code source code directly. Please refer to the original link below for detailed diagrams.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://gist.github.com/leehanchung/04c0c53fe839e6b1ad7570f026c2f988\">https://gist.github.com/leehanchung/04c0c53fe839e6b1ad7570f026c2f988</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"summary\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#summary\" aria-label=\"summary permalink\" class=\"anchor-header before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Summary</h3>\n<p>At a high level, what an agent does can be summarized as follows:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Check if it's a command</strong>: Determine whether it is a directly executable command or whether a tool needs to be invoked after analyzing the prompt</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Assess task complexity</strong>: Determine whether the task is complex enough to require the user to review a plan</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Planning</strong>: Create a plan (ToDo list) and execute it sequentially</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Determine the necessary tool for each step</strong>: Decide whether a tool (or sub-agent) is needed for the current step. If so, determine which tool is appropriate, whether permissions are available, etc.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Evaluate whether the tool usage result was adequate</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Determine whether all steps in the plan are complete</strong></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Compile and return the final response</strong></p>\n</li>\n</ol>","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#gemini-cli\">Gemini CLI</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#claude-code\">Claude Code</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#claude-code-in-detail\">Claude Code in Detail</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#summary\">Summary</a></p>\n</li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"path":"/deeplearning/25-07-28/","title":"Diagrams of Coding Agents","category":"Deep Learning","date":"2025-07-28"}}},"pageContext":{"postPath":"/deeplearning/25-07-28/","language":"eng","langRegex":"/contents/eng/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2145088972","256249292","63159454"],"slicesMap":{}}